    emmo:elucidation """The board-foot is a specialized unit of measure for the volume of lumber in the United States and Canada. It is the volume of a one-foot length of a board one foot wide and one inch thick. Board-foot can be abbreviated FBM (for 'foot, board measure'), BDFT, or BF. Thousand board-feet can be abbreviated as MFBM, MBFT or MBF.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
