    emmo:elucidation """A centimetre is a unit of length in the metric system, equal to one hundredth of a metre, which is the SI base unit of length. Centi is the SI prefix for a factor of 10.  The centimetre is the base unit of length in the now deprecated centimetre-gram-second (CGS) system of units.

