emmo:Chain a owl:NamedIndividual,
        emmo:EMMO_8246541a_f1f6_4d03_8bd7_fc6b76d17375,
        emmo:EMMO_868ae137_4d25_493e_b270_21ea3d94849e,
        emmo:EMMO_b3600e73_3e05_479d_9714_c041c3acf5cc ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/emmo/disciplines/units/specialunits-abox#>,
        "http://qudt.org/2.1/vocab/unit"^^xsd:string ;
    skos:altLabel "chain"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "Chain"@en ;
    emmo:EMMO_8189b42e_0995_423a_a26c_51168b27c3cf 2.01168e+01 ;
    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """A chain is a unit of length. It measures 66 feet, or 22 yards, or 100 links, or 4 rods. There are 10 chains in a furlong, and 80 chains in one statute mile. An acre is the area of 10 square chains (that is, an area of one chain by one furlong). The chain has been used for several centuries in Britain and in some other countries influenced by British practice.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
