    emmo:elucidation """A unit that is a non-SI unit, specifically a CGS unit,  of polarizability known informally as polarizability volume.  The SI defined units for polarizability are C*m²/V and can be converted to Ångström³ by multiplying the SI value by 4 times pi times the vacuum permittivity and then converting the resulting m³ to Ångström³ through the SI base 10 conversion (multiplying by 10⁻³⁰).

