    emmo:definition "Degree is a measurement of plane angle, defined by representing a full rotation as 360 degrees."@en ;
    emmo:elucidation """A degree (in full, a degree of arc, arc degree, or arcdegree), usually denoted by ° (the degree symbol), is a measurement of plane angle, representing 1/360 of a full rotation; one degree is equivalent to  2π /360 rad, 0.017453 rad. It is not an SI unit, as the SI unit for angles is radian, but is an accepted SI unit.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
