    emmo:EMMO_8189b42e_0995_423a_a26c_51168b27c3cf 1e-05 ;
    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """In physics, the dyne is a unit of force specified in the centimetre-gram-second (CGS) system of units. One dyne is equal to In physics, the dyne is a unit of force specified in the centimetre-gram-second (CGS) system of units. One dyne is equal to 10 micronewton. Equivalently, the dyne is defined as 'the force required to accelerate a mass of one gram at a rate of one centimetre per square second'. The dyne per centimetre is the unit traditionally used to measure surface tension.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
