emmo:Hartree a owl:NamedIndividual,
        emmo:EMMO_868ae137_4d25_493e_b270_21ea3d94849e,
        emmo:EMMO_f0404eb3_433e_48af_a50f_67f1a03f5f0c,
        emmo:EMMO_f6070071_d054_4b17_9d2d_f446f7147d0f ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/emmo/disciplines/units/specialunits-abox#>,
        "http://qudt.org/2.1/vocab/unit"^^xsd:string ;
    skos:prefLabel "Hartree"@en ;
    emmo:EMMO_8189b42e_0995_423a_a26c_51168b27c3cf 4.359744e-18 ;
    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """The `Hartree` (symbol: E_h or Ha), also known as the `Hartree Energy`, is the atomic unit of energy. The hartree energy is equal to the absolute value of the electric potential energy of the hydrogen atom in its ground state. The energy of the electron in an H-atom in its ground state is -E_H, where E_H= 2 R_∞ · hc₀. The 2006 CODATA recommended value was E_H = 4.35974394(22) × 10⁻¹⁸ J = 27.21138386(68) eV.
Definition:
E_H = e²/(4π ε₀ a₀)
where, e is the elementary charge, ε₀ is the electric constant, and a₀ is the Bohr radius.'

-- QUDT"""@en ;
    emmo:qudtReference "http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/E_h"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:unitSymbol "Ha"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:wikipediaReference "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hartree?oldid=489318053"^^xsd:string .

