    emmo:definition "A non-SI metric unit of area defined as the square with 100-metre sides."@en ;
    emmo:elucidation """The customary metric unit of land area, equal to 100 ares. One hectare is a square hectometer, that is, the area of a square 100 meters on each side: exactly 10 000 square meters or approximately 107 639.1 square feet, 11 959.9 square yards, or 2.471 054 acres.

