emmo:PlanckImpedance a owl:NamedIndividual,
        emmo:EMMO_15344998_4490_4b40_b242_c3d92e5cdc27,
        emmo:EMMO_7610efb8_c7c6_4684_abc1_774783c62472,
        emmo:EMMO_868ae137_4d25_493e_b270_21ea3d94849e,
        emmo:EMMO_b081b346_7279_46ef_9a3d_2c088fcd79f4 ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/emmo/disciplines/units/unclassifiedunits-abox#>,
        "http://qudt.org/2.1/vocab/unit"^^xsd:string ;
    skos:altLabel "Planck Impedance"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "PlanckImpedance"@en ;
    emmo:EMMO_8189b42e_0995_423a_a26c_51168b27c3cf 2.997925e+01 ;
    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """The Planck impedance is the unit of electrical resistance, denoted by Zₚ, in the system of natural units known as Planck units. The Planck impedance is directly coupled to the impedance of free space, Z₀, and differs in value from Z₀ only by a factor of 4π. If the Planck charge were instead defined to normalize the permittivity of free space, ε₀, rather than the Coulomb constant, 1/(4πε₀), then the Planck impedance would be identical to the characteristic impedance of free space.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
    emmo:qudtReference "http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/PlanckImpedance"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:unitSymbol "Zₚ"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:wikipediaReference "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planck_impedance"^^xsd:string .

emmo:PlanckLength a owl:NamedIndividual,
        emmo:EMMO_15344998_4490_4b40_b242_c3d92e5cdc27,
        emmo:EMMO_868ae137_4d25_493e_b270_21ea3d94849e,
        emmo:EMMO_b081b346_7279_46ef_9a3d_2c088fcd79f4,
        emmo:EMMO_b3600e73_3e05_479d_9714_c041c3acf5cc ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/emmo/disciplines/units/unclassifiedunits-abox#>,
        "http://qudt.org/2.1/vocab/unit"^^xsd:string ;
    skos:altLabel "Planck Length"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "PlanckLength"@en ;
    emmo:EMMO_8189b42e_0995_423a_a26c_51168b27c3cf 1.616252e-35 ;
    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """In physics, the Planck length, denoted ℓₚ, is a unit of length, equal to 1.616199(97)×10⁻³⁵ metres. It is a base unit in the system of Planck units. The Planck length can be defined from three fundamental physical constants: the speed of light in a vacuum, Planck's constant, and the gravitational constant.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
    emmo:qudtReference "http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/PlanckLength"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:unitSymbol "ℓₚ"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:wikipediaReference "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planck_units"^^xsd:string .

emmo:PlanckMass a owl:NamedIndividual,
        emmo:EMMO_15344998_4490_4b40_b242_c3d92e5cdc27,
        emmo:EMMO_77e9dc31_5b19_463e_b000_44c6e79f98aa,
        emmo:EMMO_868ae137_4d25_493e_b270_21ea3d94849e,
        emmo:EMMO_b081b346_7279_46ef_9a3d_2c088fcd79f4 ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy <https://w3id.org/emmo/disciplines/units/unclassifiedunits-abox#>,
        "http://qudt.org/2.1/vocab/unit"^^xsd:string ;
    skos:altLabel "Planck Mass"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "PlanckMass"@en ;
    emmo:EMMO_8189b42e_0995_423a_a26c_51168b27c3cf 2.17644e-08 ;
    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """In physics, the Planck mass, denoted by mₚ, is the unit of mass in the system of natural units known as Planck units. It is defined so that ≈  1.2209 × 10 GeV/c₀ = 2.17651(13) × 10 kg, (or 21.7651 μ g), where c₀ is the speed of light in a vacuum, G is the gravitational constant, and ℏ is the reduced Planck constant. Particle physicists and cosmologists often use the reduced Planck mass, which is ≈  4.341 × 10 kg = 2.435  × 10 GeV/c. The added factor of 1/{√{8π}} simplifies a number of equations in general relativity. Quantum effects are typified by the magnitude of Planck's constant.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
    emmo:qudtReference "http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/PlanckMass"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:unitSymbol "mₚ"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:wikipediaReference "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planck_units"^^xsd:string .

emmo:PlanckMomentum a owl:NamedIndividual,
        emmo:EMMO_15344998_4490_4b40_b242_c3d92e5cdc27,
        emmo:EMMO_868ae137_4d25_493e_b270_21ea3d94849e,
        emmo:EMMO_b081b346_7279_46ef_9a3d_2c088fcd79f4,
        emmo:EMMO_ec987ba8_a548_4fc9_9df6_a834daebd140 ;
