        "http://qudt.org/2.1/vocab/unit"^^xsd:string ;
    skos:altLabel "Planck Power"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "PlanckPower"@en ;
    emmo:EMMO_8189b42e_0995_423a_a26c_51168b27c3cf 3.62831e+52 ;
    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """The Planck energy divided by the Planck time is the Planck power Pₚ , equal to about 3.62831 × 10⁵² W. This is an extremely large unit; even gamma-ray bursts, the most luminous phenomena known, have output on the order of 1 × 10⁴⁵ W, less than one ten-millionth of the Planck power.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
