    emmo:elucidation """Pound per hour is a mass flow unit. It is abbreviated as PPH or more conventionally as lb/h. Fuel flow for engines is usually expressed using this unit, it is particularly useful when dealing with gases or liquids as volume flow varies more with temperature and pressure. 1 lb/h = 0.4535927 kg/h = 126.00 mg/s.  Minimum fuel intake on a jumbojet can be as low as 150 lb/h when idling, however this is not enough to sustain flight.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
    emmo:qudtReference "http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/LB-PER-HR"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:ucumCode "[lb_av].h-1"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:unitSymbol "PPH"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:wikipediaReference "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pound_per_hour?oldid=328571072"^^xsd:string .

