    emmo:elucidation """The square yard is an imperial/US customary unit of area, formerly used in most of the English-speaking world but now generally replaced by the square metre outside of the U.S. , Canada and the U.K. It is defined as the area of a square with sides of one yard in length. (Gaj in Hindi).

