    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """The standard atmosphere (symbol: atm) is an international reference pressure defined as 101.325  kPa and formerly used as unit of pressure. For practical purposes it has been replaced by the bar which is 100 kPa. The difference of about 1% is not significant for many applications, and is within the error range of common pressure gauges.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
