    emmo:elucidation """"Statampere" (statA) is a unit in the category of Electric current. It is also known as statamperes. This unit is commonly used in the cgs unit system. Statampere (statA) has a dimension of I where I is electric current. It can be converted to the corresponding standard SI unit A by multiplying its value by a factor of 3.355641E-010.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
    emmo:qudtReference "http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/A_Stat"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:unitSymbol "statA"^^xsd:string .

