        "http://qudt.org/2.1/vocab/unit"^^xsd:string ;
    skos:altLabel "Thermochemical Calorie"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "ThermochemicalCalorie"@en ;
    emmo:EMMO_8189b42e_0995_423a_a26c_51168b27c3cf 4.184e+00 ;
    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """The energy needed to increase the temperature of a given mass of water by 1 °C at atmospheric pressure depends on the starting temperature and is difficult to measure precisely. Accordingly, there have been several definitions of the calorie. The two perhaps most popular definitions used in older literature are the 15 °C calorie and the thermochemical calorie.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
