    emmo:EMMO_d088a3cb_d3e3_4eb2_9897_00aef0cb00cd 0e+00 ;
    emmo:elucidation """`Stokes (St)` is a unit in the category of Kinematic viscosity. This unit is commonly used in the cgs unit system. Stokes (St) has a dimension of L²T⁻¹ where L is length, and T is time. It can be converted to the corresponding standard SI unit m²/s by multiplying its value by a factor of 0.0001.

-- QUDT"""@en ;
