    skos:altLabel "Step"@en ;
    skos:prefLabel "TaskTile"@en ;
    emmo:conceptualisation "While a task is only an holistic part of a workflow, a task tile provide a more precise context about the placement of a task in the topological structure of a workflow by using a reductionistic categorization. A workflow is now seen as a tiling and the task is on of its tiles."@en ;
    emmo:elucidation "A task that is a well formed tile of a workflow, according to a reductionistic description."@en ;
    emmo:note "A task tile is part of a specific granularity level for the workflow description, as composition of tasks."@en .

