    skos:prefLabel "Conventional"@en ;
    emmo:OWLRL2DLAxioms "EquivalentTo: Uncoded or Coded"^^xsd:string ;
    emmo:elucidation "A 'Sign' that stands for an 'Object' through convention, norm or habit, without any resemblance to it."@en ;
    emmo:note "In Peirce semiotics this kind of sign category is called symbol. However, since symbol is also used in formal languages, the name is changed in conventional."@en .

